1 unit(s) Tofu
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
1 unit(s) Shanghai Bok Choy
1 tbsp Moo Shu Spice Blend
4 tbsp Vegetarian Oyster Sauce
1 unit(s) Carrot
4 tbsp Honey-Garlic Sauce
28 g Peanuts, chopped
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ tsp Sugar*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce. Peel, then cut carrot into 1/4-inch half-moons. Cut bok choy into 1-inch pieces.Pat tofu dry with paper towels, then cut into 1-inch pieces. Sprinkle half the Moo Shu Spice Blend over tofu, then season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add peanuts to the dry pan. Toast, stirring often, until golden, 2-3 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on peanuts so they don't burn!) Transfer to a plate.

Add 1 tbsp oil to the same pan, then tofu. (NOTE: Don't overcrowd the pan; cook tofu in 2 batches for 4 ppl, using 1 tbsp oil per batch.)  Cook, stirring occasionally, until crispy and golden-brown all over, 6-7 min.Meanwhile, add 10 cups water and 1 tbsp salt to a large pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.

Reduce heat to medium, then add carrots to the same pan. Cook, stirring often, 1-2 min. Add bok choy. Cook, stirring often, until veggies are tender-crisp, 1-2 min. Add tofu, vegetarian oyster sauce, honey-garlic sauce, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar, 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water and remaining Moo Shu Spice Blend. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens, 2-3 min. Remove from heat.

Meanwhile, add noodles to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, until tender, 1-2 min. Drain noodles, then rinse under warm water.Drain well, then return to the large pot.

Add half the peanuts and stir-fry mixture to the pot with noodles. Toss to combine. Divide noodles between bowls. Sprinkle remaining peanuts over top.